---
/**
 * Standalone claim that leads into the Método Zil section — it carries the
 * #how-we-work anchor, so it IS the head of that section, not a section of its
 * own.
 *
 * Spacing is deliberately asymmetric, and that is the rhythm working, not
 * drifting: `pt-section` gives the standard half-gap above (Projects supplies
 * the matching half), while below is ZERO. Método Zil is viewport-pinned — its
 * stage is min-h-100svh with centred content, so it already opens with
 * (100svh − content) / 2 of space above its logo, measured at ~264px on a
 * 375×812 phone. Any padding added here is stacked on top of that, which is
 * exactly what made this seam read as lopsided (128px above vs 312px below).
 * Let the pinned stage own the space below; do not add `pb-*` here.
 */
---

<section>
  <div
    class="mx-auto w-full max-w-8xl px-6 pt-section text-center tablet:px-8 desktop:px-12"
  >
    <div id="how-we-work" class="scroll-anchor"></div>
    {
      /* The marker-highlighted closing clause must always read as one unbroken
        band, so it carries `whitespace-nowrap`. That makes type size the binding
        constraint on mobile: the clause measures ~9.9px wide per 1px of font
        size, so at text-h2 it needs 342px — which fits a 390px screen exactly,
        with zero slack, and overflows every narrower phone. Hence the scale
        starts a step down: text-h3 holds it on one line to a 320px screen, and
        tablet/desktop have the room for the bigger steps. If the copy changes,
        re-check the mobile width before trusting the nowrap.

        Balancing is deliberately tablet-and-up. From tablet the clause still
        flows inline after the lead and balancing reads well, but on mobile the
        nowrap span is an atomic box wider than any word, and the balancer drags
        the preceding word onto its line to compensate — leaving that line far
        longer than the two above it (318 vs 192/204 at 390px), which is the
        opposite of balanced. Plain wrapping drops the clause onto its own line
        as a clean band instead.

        The relaxed leading is required: an inline background covers the font's
        content area (~1.26em), which is taller than the h1 token's own 1.05
        line-height, so without it the block collides with the line above. */
    }
    <h2
      class="text-[30px] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.03em] tablet:text-h2 tablet:text-balance desktop:text-h1"
    >
      Una comunicación visual con dirección clara <span
        class="bg-primary-dark px-3 whitespace-nowrap text-accent"
        >impulsa el crecimiento.</span
      >
    </h2>
  </div>
</section>
